<div id="illicit_discharge" class="SubSideContent">
    <h3>What is an illicit discharge?</h3>
                
    <p>It is any discharge to the University's stormwater system that is not totally comprised of stormwater runoff from precipitation (rainfall or snowfall) events. Examples of illicit discharge include wash water from vehicles and equipment, the cleaning of paintbrushes and mop and floor wax stripper.
    </p>
    <p>Illicit discharges are prohibited pursuant to University Administrative  Regulation AR 6:3.</p>
</div><!--/illicit_discharge-->
